  "@id": "ocp:github/bastion-rs--bastion",
  "meta": {
    "title": "bastion",
    "description": "Highly-available Distributed Fault-tolerant Runtime",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-10T20:59:55.442Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-10T20:59:55.442Z",
    "keywords": [
      "actor",
      "asynchronous",
      "concurrency",
      "distributed",
      "distributed-systems",
      "fault-tolerance",
      "hacktoberfest",
      "numa-aware",
      "rust",
      "rust-language",
      "smp",
      "supervision"
    ],
    "license": "Apache-2.0"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "* Message-based communication makes this project a lean mesh of actor system.\n    * Without web servers, weird shenanigans, forced trait implementations, and static dispatch.\n* Runtime fault-tolerance makes it a good candidate for distributed systems.\n    * If you want the smell of Erlang and the powerful aspects of Rust. That's it!\n* Completely asynchronous runtime with NUMA-aware and cache-affine SMP executor.\n    * Exploiting hardware locality wherever it is possible. It is designed for servers.\n* Supervision system makes it easy to manage lifecycles.\n    * Kill your application in certain condition or restart you subprocesses whenever a certain condition is met.\n* Automatic member discovery, cluster formation and custom message passing between cluster members.\n    * Using zeroconf or not, launch your bastion cluster from everywhere, with a single actor block.\n* Proactive IO system which doesn't depend on anything other than `futures`.\n    * Bastion's proactive IO has scatter/gather operations, `io_uring` support and much more...",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
